cell.name: MainenNeuroML
cell.meta:notes:
Complete description of cell model in neuroConstruct's internal data model, which has a one to one mapping with NeuroML.
Note, a few fixes to the original morphology were needed:
Sections with zero start/end radius were given 0.01 um radius. Segments with zero length had their end points shifted by 0.001 um in the x dir to create a real segment with negligible extra area.
There are some slight differences in simulations run with this morphology and those run with the original simulation code due to NEURON reconnecting dendrites which -float in space-, i.e. where the specified start point on a section doesn't exactly match the location it's connected to on its parent section. This reconnection seems to change the area of some segments (iseg in particular)

meta:property.meta:value: Recompartmentalisation comment: Not splitting, as electrotonic length is unlikely to be an issue, and all 3D detail is usually needed as dends, stims connection location might have big impact on stimulation
